151
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:28,722
Because Dissue Alassondoes not answer the phone

152
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:30,640
for just anyone,

153
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:33,476
Bobby face.

154
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:38,232
Ish now time to do whatever it ish I do.

155
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:39,983
Aren't you a fashion designer?

156
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:43,528
You know me so well.

157
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:54,789
I can blow up those balloons, grandma.

158
00:06:54,873 --> 00:06:56,499
I have strong lungs.

159
00:06:56,583 --> 00:07:01,462
I once played Moby Dick and wasunderwater for six hours.

160
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:03,798
Okay. I picked up the cake.

161
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:06,634
I may or may not have dipped my finger

162
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:09,596
in a frosting walrus.

163
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,932
Whew!

164
00:07:12,015 --> 00:07:13,808
Tough day at the old office.

165
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:15,769
[all] Surprise!

166
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:18,063
Mom, what are you doing here?

167
00:07:18,146 --> 00:07:20,274
I brought her in so we couldall spend some time together.

168
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:23,277
You don't look surprised.

169
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,320
Here, let me help you.

170
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:29,699
We'll rehearse that later.

171
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:33,120
Nice to see you, mom,
but I got to run back to work.

172
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:35,580
There's a real walrus who wants my job.

173
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:38,458
He's good. He's real good.

174
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:41,669
It's weird seeing dad out
of the house during the day.

175
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:43,130
Yeah.

176
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:45,590
I hope they're not just paying him in fish.

177
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:47,842
It's happened before.

178
00:07:47,926 --> 00:07:49,928
I'm happy for my son.

179
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:51,888
He's off to the aquarium.

180
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:55,683
Those are just two of the films I did in '64.

181
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:58,437
Who wants tea?

182
00:07:58,519 --> 00:08:00,188
What year did you make that film?

183
00:08:00,272 --> 00:08:03,817
Oh, no, I was just asking if you wanted tea.

184
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,068
Don't be dense, dear.

185
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:11,283
Grandma... your wig fell off.

186
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:13,410
What? I don't wear a wig.

187
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:14,828
Then your completely natural hair

188
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:16,204
is just hanging on the light.

189
00:08:16,288 --> 00:08:18,790
- Barb?- Ah! Oh!

190
