191
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,877
He'll leave me for Ethel

192
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:24,421
from the yoga class.

193
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:26,547
He's always commenting how limber she is.

194
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:28,425
She can bend over and touch her knees.

195
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:32,429
both: Hey!

196
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:33,513
Sigmund.

197
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,640
Hey, Barb.

198
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:38,518
It's Harper, her granddaughter.

199
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:41,980
But her stress lines do make her look 70.

200
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:44,941
So you want to tour the grounds?

201
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:46,526
I have a tree house.

202
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:50,822
Ooh. A location scout.

203
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:53,783
Now, who wants to carry me?

204
00:08:56,286 --> 00:08:58,455
Harper, just set Sigmund down by the door.

205
00:09:00,832 --> 00:09:03,126
You are carrying him back down.

206
00:09:06,338 --> 00:09:08,256
both: Dad?

207
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:10,300
What are you doing here?

208
00:09:10,384 --> 00:09:12,344
Welcome to the aquarium!

209
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:18,183
Dad, why would you lie to usabout having a job?

210
00:09:18,266 --> 00:09:20,560
Because I don't want to spenda week with my mom.

211
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:22,645
All she thinks about is herself.

212
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:25,899
Plus I spent $7,000on this walrus costume.

213
00:09:28,235 --> 00:09:31,279
Dad, grandma Barb loves you.

214
00:09:31,363 --> 00:09:32,864
No, she doesn't.

215
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,700
