my third grade talent show.

216
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:38,453
It was 1983 when...

217
00:09:40,788 --> 00:09:44,834
What are you waiting for?Tell the story already.

218
00:09:44,918 --> 00:09:46,586
Sorry.

219
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:50,715
So I had spent months preparing
this cutting-edge dance routine,

220
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,675
but when I finally took the stage,

221
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:54,719
she was nowhere to be seen.

222
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:56,804
I burst into tears and I ran out of the building,

223
00:09:56,888 --> 00:09:59,640
and I haven't set foot in a school since.

224
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:03,061
Well, did you tell grandma how upset you were?

225
00:10:03,144 --> 00:10:04,563
No.

226
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:06,981
And promise me that you won't either.

227
00:10:07,065 --> 00:10:08,567
I know how much you guys love her,

228
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:10,235
and how much she loves you,

229
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:12,487
and I don't want this
to hurt your relationship.

230
00:10:12,571 --> 00:10:14,739
I'm just not ready to forgive her.

231
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:16,157
Cut!

232
00:10:16,241 --> 00:10:19,244
I didn't believe a word you just said.

233
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:23,081
Let's try that again, but with feeling!

234
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,709
[in garbled foreign accent]
Zere!

235
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:29,963
You look fabulous!

236
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:32,132
It's definitely unique.

237
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:35,260
Ish "amashing."

238
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:38,846
I guess it is "amashing."

239
00:10:38,930 --> 00:10:40,848
What is going on here?

240
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:42,601
Who is this person

241
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:45,562
